{
  "stem": "2713.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the train stopped, and they brought-- this fellow was lying just there and still alive, blood everywhere.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was just unbelievable that they could leave him like this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We begged them, why don't you kill him?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "After a while, they shot him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we still didn't know where we're going.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in our mind, if they-- if they want us to be alive, they would give us food.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That means we are going somewhere-- or just they're doing it on purpose so we'd be finished off.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When we were traveling for 15 days, we were very lucky, I must say again, because in my train where I was in the carriage there, there was with us a German who was a kapo in the camp.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was one who didn't believe in Hitler as well, so he was in the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And another kapo was who was not supposed to be Jewish, but he was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I will tell you after the story that I found out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they managed to, in Czechoslovakia when we were traveling back and forwards, on a station, they managed to buy a little bit of sugar in a bag.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this sugar was given to us afterwards, every day a tiny little spoon like a teaspoon.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so I can't say that I didn't eat for 15 days, because afterwards I had every day a little-- one little spoon of sugar.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was my meal for 15 days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] People from Czechoslovakia were coming close to our train nearly every day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They found out that we are there in the train, and they begged them to give us food, because they-- they brought food.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
